data.name: Label1.Text
data.value:
Bad Company 2 HitFixer 2 is a program which try to fix the hit registration problems in Bad Company 2.
If you're having trouble hitting your enemies then you should try this.
It's very simple: 1) Insert your server browser ping in the text box 2) Check the "First Time" checkbox if it's the first time - Uncheck if you've already run this program 3) Press the "Quick Fix" button and play the game 4) Press the "Default" button to undo any change

data.name: Label11.Text
data.value:
Thanks for downloading and using Bad Company 2 HitFixer 2. The purpose of this program is to fix (or at least try to fix) the hit registration problems which afflict Bad Company 2 and previous games from DICE.
If you've downloaded this program and you're using it then most likely you're experiencing problems with the netcode. You should not consider BC2HF2 as a total fix for the hit registration, it'll just limit the cases of bad registration.
Why it can't be consider as a total fix? Because there are too many factors , like your connection and the enemies one, which make the fix not total but partial. For sure you'll se an impovment but you still can see some fails.
Remember this program is completely free and was made during free time by a no-professional programmer, so you may find some bugs. If you find any please report them to the creator.
Bad Company 2 HitFixer 2 is made by Andrea 'Dendari' Marini based on Battlefield 2/21242 HitFixer. Credits go to Guy.Buddy.Friend from BF2S forums.
